        <Parent_String>Mesopotamian (culture or style) [300019828], Near Eastern (Early Western World) [300019571], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a period and style in Mesopotamia from about 2150 to 2112 BCE, between the end of the Akkadian Empire and the start of the Third Dynasty of Ur. Used in particular to describe the sculptural style of Gudea of Lagash and cylinder seals of the period; however the dates of the reign of Gudea are now debated.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a un período y estilo en Mesopotamia de aproximadamente 2150 al 2112 a.C., entre el fin del Imperio Acadio y el comienzo de la III Dinastía de Ur. Usado para describir el estilo escultórico de Gudea de Lagash y sellos de cilindro del período; sin embargo, actualmente las fechas del reino de Gudea son debatidas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de periode en stijl in Mesopotamië van circa 2150 tot 2112 v. Chr., tussen het einde van het Akkadische rijk en het begin van de Derde Dynastie van Ur. Met name te gebruiken om de stijl van de beeldhouwkunst van Gudea van Lagash en de rolzegels uit deze periode te beschrijven. De regeerperiode van Gudea wordt momenteel echter weer ter discussie gesteld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指自西元前2150年至西元前2112年間，於美索不達米亞發展的時代與風格，此時代介於阿卡德王朝末年與烏爾（Ur）第三王朝之始。用於特別指稱拉格什的古地亞（Gudea of Lagash）統治下流行之雕塑風格，以及此時代的圓筒圖章，然而，目前對於古地亞統治時期的斷代多有爭論。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
